Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, significant proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal). Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, suggesting non-diabetic glucosuria. These findings are suggestive of renal dysfunction, possibly tubular injury or glomerulopathy. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for underlying causes. No evidence of urinary tract infection.
